<p>--<a href="http://www.goodreads.com/quotes/show/174247" rel="nofollow">G. Khan</a></p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2kd1"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2kd1" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2kd1')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2kd1" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2kd1')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2kd1" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2o3/rationality_quotes_september_2010/2kd1?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2kd1" href="#2kcv" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2kd1" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2kd1')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2kd1 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2kd1" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_2kd1" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_2kd1" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2khm" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2khm" class="parent"><a name="2khm" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2khm" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2khm" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2khm" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/James_K/">James_K</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">06 September 2010 07:29:08AM</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2khm'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2khm')">[+] (6 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2khm" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2khm" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/James_K/">James_K</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">06 September 2010 07:29:08AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2khm'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2khm'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2khm')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2khm" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>G. Khan?  That's the first time I've seen a title abbreviated that way.</p>

<p>It is a good quote in a "rationality is about winning" sort of way.  Such a shame is definition of winning was so negative sum.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2khm"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2khm" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2khm')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2khm" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2khm')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2khm" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2o3/rationality_quotes_september_2010/2khm?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2khm" href="#2kd1" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2khm" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2khm')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2khm class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2khm" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_2khm" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_2khm" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2kk6" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2kk6" class="parent"><a name="2kk6" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2kk6" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2kk6" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2kk6" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Perplexed/">Perplexed</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">06 September 2010 04:22:56PM</span><span class="votes " >3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2kk6'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2kk6')">[+] (5 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2kk6" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2kk6" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Perplexed/">Perplexed</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">06 September 2010 04:22:56PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2kk6'>3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2kk6'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2kk6')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2kk6" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Is it permissible to assert that rationality is about winning?   Hume might argue that "winning" is about ends, whereas "rationality" is about means.</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>Reason is, and ought only to be, the slave of the passions, and can never pretend to any other office than to serve and obey them.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>-- D. Hume</p>

<p>However, it is sometimes argued that the word "rational" can be applied to ends, as well as means.</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>[M]ost preference logicians hold that any logic suitable to this purpose must assume that all <em>rational</em> preference orderings are transitive.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>--<a href="http://www.jstor.org/pss/2219832" rel="nofollow">M. Phipps in &quot;Must Rational Preferences Be Transitive?&quot;</a></p>

<p>It appears that Mr. Khan's expressed preferences are very likely transitive, but it is difficult to see how this could be argued regarding Mr. Bagehot's preferences.  Unlike Mr Khan, Mr Bagehot makes his own desires dependent upon the expressed opinions of those around him.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2kk6"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2kk6" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2kk6')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2kk6" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2kk6')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2kk6" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2o3/rationality_quotes_september_2010/2kk6?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2kk6" href="#2khm" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2kk6" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2kk6')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2kk6 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2kk6" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_2kk6" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_2kk6" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2ms2" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2ms2" class="parent"><a name="2ms2" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2ms2" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2ms2" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2ms2" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/wedrifid/">wedrifid</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">17 September 2010 08:30:47AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2ms2'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2ms2')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2ms2" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2ms2" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/wedrifid/">wedrifid</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">17 September 2010 08:30:47AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2ms2'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2ms2'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2ms2')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2ms2" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>Is it permissible to assert that rationality is about winning? Hume might argue that "winning" is about ends, whereas "rationality" is about means.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>You're right. And the "rationalist win" slogan gets annoying for that reason - a good point but not technically correct. There's something along the lines of 'most likely' or 'maximise' that is missing.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2ms2"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2ms2" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2ms2')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2ms2" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2ms2')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2ms2" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2o3/rationality_quotes_september_2010/2ms2?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2ms2" href="#2kk6" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2ms2" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2ms2')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2ms2 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2ms2" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2ms1" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2ms1" class="parent"><a name="2ms1" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2ms1" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2ms1" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2ms1" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/wedrifid/">wedrifid</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">17 September 2010 08:29:34AM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2ms1'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2ms1')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2ms1" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2ms1" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/wedrifid/">wedrifid</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">17 September 2010 08:29:34AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2ms1'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2ms1'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2ms1')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2ms1" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>Unlike Mr Khan, Mr Bagehot makes his own desires dependent upon the expressed opinions of those around him.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>Wow. I've never comparison to Gengis Khan used as a way to make someone sound fickle. :)</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2ms1"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2ms1" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2ms1')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2ms1" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2ms1')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2ms1" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2o3/rationality_quotes_september_2010/2ms1?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2ms1" href="#2kk6" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2ms1" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2ms1')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2ms1 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2ms1" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2koy" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2koy" class="parent"><a name="2koy" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2koy" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2koy" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2koy" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/James_K/">James_K</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">07 September 2010 05:40:50AM</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2koy'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2koy')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2koy" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2koy" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/James_K/">James_K</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">07 September 2010 05:40:50AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2koy'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2koy'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2koy')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2koy" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Eliezer advocates the "rationality is about winning" position, as timtyler note sin his reply to you.</p>

<p>And this is actually a Humean point.  The idea is that passion is about what you want i.e. want qualifies as winning and rationality is about getting what you want i.e. how to go about winning.</p>

<p>As for Mr Bagehot's preference set, it's true that transitivity is a necessary condition for rationality because an agent with intransitive preferences has no coherent utility function.</p>

<p>However, I don't think that's an issue here.  Bagehot's preferences are dependant on others, but that doesn't make them intransitive.  I fact there's no way to test for intransitivity with fewer than three alternatives to choose from.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2koy"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2koy" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2koy')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2koy" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2koy')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2koy" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2o3/rationality_quotes_september_2010/2koy?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2koy" href="#2kk6" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2koy" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2koy')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2koy class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2koy" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2klk" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2klk" class="parent"><a name="2klk" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2klk" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2klk" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2klk" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/timtyler/">timtyler</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">06 September 2010 07:07:59PM</span><span class="votes " >3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2klk'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2klk')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2klk" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2klk" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/timtyler/">timtyler</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">06 September 2010 07:07:59PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2klk'>3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2klk'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2klk')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2klk" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>That's a Yudkowsky theme:</p>

<p><a href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/7i/rationality_is_systematized_winning/" rel="nofollow">http://lesswrong.com/lw/7i/rationality_is_systematized_winning/</a></p>

<p><a href="http://wiki.lesswrong.com/wiki/Rationalists_should_win" rel="nofollow">http://wiki.lesswrong.com/wiki/Rationalists_should_win</a></p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2klk"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2klk" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2klk')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2klk" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2klk')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2klk" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2o3/rationality_quotes_september_2010/2klk?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2klk" href="#2kk6" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2klk" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2klk')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2klk class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2klk" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2klp" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2klp" class="parent"><a name="2klp" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2klp" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2klp" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2klp" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Will_Sawin/">Will_Sawin</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">06 September 2010 07:16:36PM</span><span class="votes " >0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2klp'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2klp')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2klp" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2klp" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Will_Sawin/">Will_Sawin</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">06 September 2010 07:16:36PM</span><span class="vo