 points', '21 points', '22 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2khe')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2khe" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>I had, also, during many years followed a golden rule, namely, that whenever a published fact, a new observation or thought came across me, which was opposed to my general results, to make a memorandum of it without fail and at once; for I had found by experience that such facts and thoughts were far more apt to escape from the memory than favourable ones. Owing to this habit, very few objections were raised against my views which I had not at least noticed and attempted to answer.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>-From his <a href="http://www.stephenjaygould.org/library/darwin_autobiography.html" rel="nofollow">Autobiography</a>, 1902.</p>

<p>A wonderful quote indeed. Found by guessing that it was biographical or autobiographical (it seemed a little too personal for a scientific treatise) and searching for the word "fact" in the online text of the (very readable) autobiography.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2khe"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2khe" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2khe')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2khe" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2khe')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2khe" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2o3/rationality_quotes_september_2010/2khe?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2khe" href="#2k9l" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2khe" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2khe')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2khe class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2khe" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_2khe" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_2khe" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2ktm" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2ktm" class="parent"><a name="2ktm" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2ktm" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2ktm" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2ktm" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RobinZ/">RobinZ</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">08 September 2010 02:06:25AM</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2ktm'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2ktm')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2ktm" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2ktm" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RobinZ/">RobinZ</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">08 September 2010 02:06:25AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2ktm'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2ktm'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2ktm')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2ktm" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>If I could give an additional upvote for your elaboration of methodology, I would.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2ktm"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2ktm" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2ktm')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2ktm" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2ktm')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2ktm" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2o3/rationality_quotes_september_2010/2ktm?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2ktm" href="#2khe" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2ktm" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2ktm')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2ktm class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2ktm" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2ka5" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2ka5" class="parent"><a name="2ka5" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2ka5" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2ka5" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2ka5" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Perplexed/">Perplexed</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">04 September 2010 09:49:44PM</span><span class="votes " >3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2ka5'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2ka5')">[+] (2 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2ka5" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2ka5" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Perplexed/">Perplexed</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">04 September 2010 09:49:44PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2ka5'>3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2ka5'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2ka5')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2ka5" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>As society and the problems that face it become more and more complex and machines become more and more intelligent, people will let machines make more of their decisions for them, simply because machine-made decisions will bring better results than man-made ones. Eventually a stage may be reached at which the decisions necessary to keep the system running will be so complex that human beings will be incapable of making them intelligently. At that stage the machines will be in effective control. People won't be able to just turn the machines off, because they will be so dependent on them that turning them off would amount to suicide.</p>

<p>T. Kaczynski
as quoted by R. Kurzweil
<a href="http://www.wired.com/wired/archive/8.04/joy.html" rel="nofollow">as quoted in turn by Bill Joy</a></p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2ka5"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2ka5" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2ka5')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2ka5" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2ka5')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2ka5" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2o3/rationality_quotes_september_2010/2ka5?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2ka5" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2ka5')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2ka5 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2ka5" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_2ka5" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_2ka5" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2kf9" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2kf9" class="parent"><a name="2kf9" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2kf9" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2kf9" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2kf9" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/AlanCrowe/">AlanCrowe</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">05 September 2010 09:26:42PM</span><span class="votes " >7 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2kf9'] = ['6 points', '7 points', '8 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2kf9')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2kf9" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2kf9" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/AlanCrowe/">AlanCrowe</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">05 September 2010 09:26:42PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2kf9'>7 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2kf9'] = ['6 points', '7 points', '8 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2kf9')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2kf9" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Since 1900, perhaps 1800 or even earlier, people have been letting markets make their decisions for them. When the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bolshevik" rel="nofollow">Bolsheviks</a> decided to turn off the markets by bringing the means of production and exchange into common ownership they found that the decisions necessary to keep the system running were so complex that human beings were incapable of making them intelligently.</p>

<p>That is Mises <a href="http://mises.org/econcalc.asp" rel="nofollow">Economic calculation</a> argument against socialism. Perhaps Mises argument is wrong. Free markets and private property offer a system that is roughly incentive compatible. Perhaps the real issue is that we do not know how to design a burearocracy in which the incentives of the bureaucrats are sufficiently aligned with the over-arching goal. Whatever. My main point is that people only make decisions locally and have never been in charge in the sense that quote claims.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2kf9"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2kf9" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2kf9')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2kf9" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2kf9')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2kf9" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2o3/rationality_quotes_september_2010/2kf9?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2kf9" href="#2ka5" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2kf9" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2kf9')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2kf9 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2kf9" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_2kf9" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_2kf9" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2kfm" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2kfm" class="parent"><a name="2kfm" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2kfm" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2kfm" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2kfm" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Perplexed/">Perplexed</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">05 September 2010 10:38:18PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2kfm'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2kfm')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2kfm" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2kfm" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Perplexed/">Perplexed</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">05 September 2010 10:38:18PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2kfm'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2kfm'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2kfm')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2kfm" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>My main point is that people only make decisions locally and have never been in charge in the sense that quote claims.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>Perhaps not, but in the past, whenever folks have become too dissatisfied with the non-local decisions being made on their behalf, they have always managed to find some scapegoat to put up against the wall and shoot.  And that catharsis, while costly, never quite reached the level of stupidity of a collective suicide.</p>

<p>I almost agree with the Unibomber here.  I hope we never become so dependent on our technology that we simply can't find our way back.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2kfm"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2kfm" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2kfm')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2kfm" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2kfm')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2kfm" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2o3/rationality_quotes_september_2010/2kfm?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2kfm" href="#2kf9" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2kfm" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2kfm')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2kfm class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2kfm" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2k8z" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2k8z" class="parent"><a name="2k8z" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2k8z" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2k8z" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2k8z" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/DanielVarga/">DanielVarga</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">04 September 2010 03:39:33PM</span><span class="votes " >4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2k8z'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2k8z')">[+] (3 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2k8z" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2k8z" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/DanielVarga/">DanielVarga</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">04 September 2010 03:39:33PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2k8z'>4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2k8z'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2k8z')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2k8z" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>Von Neumann advised Shannon to use the word “entropy” on the grounds that “Nobody knows what entropy really is, so in a debate you will always have the advantage.”</p>
</blockquote>

<p><a href="http://gowers.wordpress.com/2010/08/22/icm2010-villani-laudatio/" rel="nofollow">Gowers quoting H-T Yau quoting Shannon quoting von Neumann</a></p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2k8z"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2k8z" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2k8z')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2k8z" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2k8z')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2k8z" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2o3/rationality_quotes_september_2010/2k8z?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2k8z" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2k8z')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2k8z class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2k8z" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_2k8z" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_2k8z" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2k93" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2k93" class="parent"><a name="2k93" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2k93" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2k93" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2k93" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/wnoise/">wnoise</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">04 September 2010 04:42:49PM</span><span class="votes " >3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2k93'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2k93')">[+] (2 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2k93" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2k93" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/wnoise/">wnoise</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">04 September 2010 04:42:49PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2k93'>3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2k93'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2k93')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2k93" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Well, there's also the issue that they're fundamentally the same thing.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2k93"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2k93" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2k93')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2k93" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2k93')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2k93" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2o3/rationality_quotes_september_2010/2k93?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2k93" href="#2k8z" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2k93" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2k93')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2k93 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2k93" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_2k93" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_2k93" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2k9c" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2k9c" class="parent"><a name="2k9c" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2k9c" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2k9c" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2k9c" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/DanielVarga/">DanielVarga</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">04 September 2010 05:26:34PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2k9c'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2k9c')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2k9c" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2k9c" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/DanielVarga/">DanielVarga</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">04 September 2010 05:26:34PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2k9c'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2k9c'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2k9c')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2k9c" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>This is hindsight. In 1948, Shannon and von Neumann were obviously aware of a deep analogy, but nothing more than that. The position you take was made popular by Jaynes only in 1957, nine years later.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2k9c"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2k9c" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2k9c')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2k9c" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2k9c')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2k9c" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2o3/rationality_quotes_september_2010/2k9c?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2k9c" href="#2k93" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2k9c" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2k9c')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2k9c class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2k9c" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_2k9c" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_2k9c" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2k9g" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2k9g" class="parent"><a name="2k9g" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2k9g" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2k9g" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2k9g" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/wnoise/">wnoise</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">04 September 2010 05:43:52PM</span><span class="votes " >0 point