nt('t1_2jlg')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2jlg" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>That seems like the extreme case of "you don't really understand something until you can explain it to somebody else", which I'm sure somebody other than me must have said a long time ago.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2jlg"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2jlg" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2jlg')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2jlg" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2jlg')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2jlg" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2o3/rationality_quotes_september_2010/2jlg?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2jlg" href="#2jkm" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2jlg" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2jlg')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2jlg class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2jlg" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_2jlg" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_2jlg" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2jmt" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2jmt" class="parent"><a name="2jmt" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2jmt" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2jmt" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2jmt" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/gwern/">gwern</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 September 2010 01:03:57PM</span><span class="votes " >13 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2jmt'] = ['12 points', '13 points', '14 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2jmt')">[+] (4 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2jmt" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2jmt" href="http://lesswrong.c