pe="text/javascript">vl['t1_2jo1'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2jo1')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2jo1" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Of course, machine learning algorithms render this obsolete.  You don't have to understand something to program it, just have a vague understanding of how that understanding might come about.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2jo1"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2jo1" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2jo1')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2jo1" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2jo1')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2jo1" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2o3/rationality_quotes_september_2010/2jo1?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2jo1" href="#2jmt" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2jo1" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2jo1')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2jo1 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2jo1" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_2jo1" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_2jo1" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2job" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2job" class="parent"><a name="2job" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2job" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2job" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2job" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/gwern/">gwern</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 September 2010 03:06:47PM</span><span class="votes " >5 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2job'] = ['4 points', '5 points', '6 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2job')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2job" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2job" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/gwern/">gwern</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 September 2010 03:06:47PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2job'>5 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2job'] = ['4 points', '5 points', '6 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2job')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2job" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Arguably, that's still understanding. 'Now I know that natural language parsing is in this family of parametric functions which my ML algorithm can handle, with the coefficients given by minimizing the divergence from a bazillion word corpus...&amp;etc.'</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2job"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2job" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2job')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2job" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2job')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2job" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2o3/rationality_quotes_september_2010/2job?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2job" href="#2jo1" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2job" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2job')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2job class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2job" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2jog" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2jog" class="parent"><a name="2jog" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2jog" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2jog" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2jog" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/SilasBarta/">SilasBarta</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 September 2010 03:22:40PM</span><span class="votes " >3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2jog'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2jog')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2jog" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2jog" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/SilasBarta/">SilasBarta</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 September 2010 03:22:40PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2jog'>3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2jog'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2jog')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2jog" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>If that could work, that would be equivalent to having a <a href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1yq/understanding_your_understanding/">Level 3</a> understanding of how to regenerate the required knowledge -- hardly a shortcut!</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2jog"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2jog" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2jog')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2jog" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2jog')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2jog" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2o3/rationality_quotes_september_2010/2jog?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2jog" href="#2jo1" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2jog" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2jog')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2jog class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2jog" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2kdg" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2kdg" class="parent"><a name="2kdg" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2kdg" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2kdg" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2kdg" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/DanielLC/">DanielLC</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">05 September 2010 05:42:44PM</span><span class="votes " >0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2kdg'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2kdg')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2kdg" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2kdg" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/DanielLC/">DanielLC</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">05 September 2010 05:42:44PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2kdg'>0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2kdg'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2kdg')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2kdg" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>No, you have to have a certain understanding of how that understanding might come about.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2kdg"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2kdg" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2kdg')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2kdg" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2kdg')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2kdg" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2o3/rationality_quotes_september_2010/2kdg?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2kdg" href="#2jo1" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2kdg" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2kdg')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2kdg class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2kdg" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2joe" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2joe" class="parent"><a name="2joe" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2joe" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2joe" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2joe" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/SilasBarta/">SilasBarta</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 September 2010 03:16:23PM</span><span class="votes " >7 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2joe'] = ['6 points', '7 points', '8 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2joe')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2joe" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2joe" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/SilasBarta/">SilasBarta</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 September 2010 03:16:23PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2joe'>7 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2joe'] = ['6 points', '7 points', '8 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2joe')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2joe" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Yes, and explaining it to a computer (i.e. writing working code) is the hardest version of this test, because it's the closest thing to a blank slate -- you can't rely on anything being "understood" like you would with a person, in which case you can just start from the NePOCU (nearest point of common understanding, learn to live with the acronym).</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2joe"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2joe" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2joe')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2joe" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2joe')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2joe" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2o3/rationality_quotes_september_2010/2joe?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2joe" href="#2jlg" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2joe" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2joe')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2joe class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2joe" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2jlm" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2jlm" class="parent"><a name="2jlm" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2jlm" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2jlm" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2jlm" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Morendil/">Morendil</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 September 2010 10:18:39AM</span><span class="votes " >13 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2jlm'] = ['12 points', '13 points', '14 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2jlm')">[+] (5 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2jlm" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2jlm" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Morendil/">Morendil</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 September 2010 10:18:39AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2jlm'>13 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2jlm'] = ['12 points', '13 points', '14 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2jlm')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2jlm" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Yes! I'm happy that at least one person <a href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1mh/that_magical_click/">clicks</a> on that.</p>

<p>The software industry is currently held back by a conception of programming-as-manual-labor, consisting of semi-mechanically turning a specification document into executable code. In fact it's much closer to "the art of improving your understanding of some business domain by expressing the details of that domain in a formal notation". The resulting program isn't quite a by-product of that activity - it's important, though not nearly as important as distilling the domain understanding.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2jlm"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2jlm" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2jlm')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2jlm" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2jlm')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2jlm" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2o3/rationality_quotes_september_2010/2jlm?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2jlm" href="#2jlg" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2jlm" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2jlm')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2jlm class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2jlm" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_2jlm" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_2jlm" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2k0k" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2k0k" class="parent"><a name="2k0k" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2k0k" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2k0k" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2k0k" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/CronoDAS/">CronoDAS</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 September 2010 11:36:13PM</span><span class="votes " >6 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2k0k'] = ['5 points', '6 points', '7 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2k0k')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2k0k" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2k0k" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/CronoDAS/">CronoDAS</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 September 2010 11:36:13PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2k0k'>6 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2k0k'] = ['5 points', '6 points', '7 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2k0k')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2k0k" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Programming is the art of figuring out what you want so precisely that you can tell even a machine how to do it.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2k0k"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2k0k" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2k0k')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2k0k" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2k0k')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2k0k" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2o3/rationality_quotes_september_2010/2k0k?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2k0k" href="#2jlm" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2k0k" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2k0k')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2k0k class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2k0k" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2jtr" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2jtr" class="parent"><a name="2jtr" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2jtr" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2jtr" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2jtr" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/ShardPhoenix/">ShardPhoenix</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 September 2010 04:00:54AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2jtr'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2jtr')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2jtr" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2jtr" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/ShardPhoenix/">ShardPhoenix</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 September 2010 04:00:54AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2jtr'>4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2jtr'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2jtr')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2jtr" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>While that's basically true, a significant part of any large program consists of dealing with "accidental complexity" that isn't really part of the "business logic". Of course in many cases that only makes the programming even less mechanical.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2jtr"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2jtr" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2jtr')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2jtr" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2jtr')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2jtr" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2o3/rationality_quotes_september_2010/2jtr?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2jtr" href="#2jlm" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2jtr" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2jtr')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2jtr class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2jtr" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2jof" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2jof" class="parent"><a name="2jof" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2jof" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2jof" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2jof" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/SilasBarta/">SilasBarta</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 September 2010 03:18:53PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >5 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2jof'] = ['4 points', '5 points', '6 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2jof')">[+] (2 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2jof" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2jof" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/SilasBarta/">SilasBarta</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 September 2010 03:18:53PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2jof'>5 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2jof'] = ['4 points', '5 points', '6 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2jof')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2jof" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Yes, I agree.  The real test of AI is <em>not</em> the automation of "formal specification -&gt; working code" -- if the client could formalize it to that level, they could write the code themselves.  Rather, the real test is whether an AI could talk to an extroverted MBA, figure out what they want, and then produce the working code.  But so far, only humans programmers can do that.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2jof"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2jof" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2jof')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2jof" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2jof')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2jof" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2o3/rationality_quotes_september_2010/2jof?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2jof" href="#2jlm" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2jof" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2jof')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2jof class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2jof" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_2jof" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_2jof" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2joj" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2joj" class="parent"><a name="2joj" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2joj" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2joj" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2joj" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Morendil/">Morendil</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 September 2010 03:31:31PM</span><span class="votes " >15 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2joj'] = ['14 points', '15 points', '16 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2joj')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2joj" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2joj" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Morendil/">Morendil</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 September 2010 03:31:31PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2joj'>15 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2joj'] = ['14 points', '15 points', '16 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2joj')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2joj" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>And by the same token, we'll know we've nailed AI <em>not</em> when we have written a program that can have that conversation... but when we have written down an account of how we are able to have that conversation, to such a level of detail that there's nothing left to explain.</p>

<p>Writing a program which solves the Towers of Hanoi is not too hard. Proving, given a formalization of the ToH, various properties of a program that solves it, isn't too hard. But <em>looking at a bunch of wooden disks slotted on pegs</em> and coming up with an interpretation of <em>that</em> situation which corresponds to the abstract scheme we know as "Towers of Hanoi"... That's where the fun is.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2joj"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2joj" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2joj')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2joj" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2joj')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2joj" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2o3/rationality_quotes_september_2010/2joj?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2joj" href="#2jof" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2joj" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2joj')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2joj class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2joj" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_2joj" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_2joj" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2ju3" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2ju3" class="parent"><a name="2ju3" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2ju3" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2ju3" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2ju3" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Theist/">Theist</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 September 2010 04:18:43AM</span><span class="votes " >3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2ju3'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2ju3')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2ju3" class="" ><div class="commen